And it's US per capita energy.

00:11:18.700 --> 00:11:21.633
And the units are in watts.

00:11:21.633 --> 00:11:24.967
So it's the rate at which
we're using energy for a

00:11:24.967 --> 00:11:27.667
variety of different purposes.

00:11:27.667 --> 00:11:29.700
And I'll run through some of
it, but I won't go through

00:11:29.700 --> 00:11:30.367
every detail.

00:11:30.367 --> 00:11:37.733
So here's oil, biomass,
coal, natural gas.

00:11:37.733 --> 00:11:42.033
Obviously, oil, coal, and
natural gas are the bigger

00:11:42.033 --> 00:11:43.900
inputs here.

00:11:43.900 --> 00:11:47.167
There's geothermal, wind, hydro,
nuclear, and solar up

00:11:47.167 --> 00:11:49.400
at the top as well.

00:11:49.400 --> 00:11:52.433
Now, they've got a separate
branch at the top for

00:11:52.433 --> 00:11:55.100
electricity production.

00:11:55.100 --> 00:11:58.200
Everything that's going to
be used by first making

00:11:58.200 --> 00:12:03.933
electricity goes up to
this top area here.

00:12:03.933 --> 00:12:08.500
And we see that a little bit of
oil is used for that, but a

00:12:08.500 --> 00:12:09.767
lot of coal.

00:12:09.767 --> 00:12:13.767
In fact, almost all the coal
that's used in this country is

00:12:13.767 --> 00:12:15.000
used for making electricity.

00:12:17.633 --> 00:12:22.967
A lot of natural gas, some
geothermal, wind, hydro.

00:12:22.967 --> 00:12:26.133
All the hydro is used
for electricity.

00:12:26.133 --> 00:12:28.833
All the nuclear is used
for electricity.

00:12:28.833 --> 00:12:31.767
All the solar is used
for electricity.

00:12:31.767 --> 00:12:40.300
Of the 4,400 watts per capita
that's used for electricity

00:12:40.300 --> 00:12:48.833
production, 3,000 is lost as
waste, energy waste, usually

00:12:48.833 --> 00:12:51.867
in the form of heat.

00:12:51.867 --> 00:12:57.333
And about 1,400 is used for
residential, commercial,

00:12:57.333 --> 00:13:01.967
industrial, and even a tiny
bit for transportation.

00:13:01.967 --> 00:13:03.867
So you see how the
diagram works.

00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:08.833
And then over at the right-hand
side, it has

