transmission loss.

00:13:57.967 --> 00:14:00.333
If you have a power plant
where you're making

00:14:00.333 --> 00:14:02.967
electricity, and then you have
to send it over power lines to

00:14:02.967 --> 00:14:04.667
get it to the consumer,
there's going

00:14:04.667 --> 00:14:06.867
to be loss in that.

00:14:06.867 --> 00:14:09.833
And then there's going to be
some--if you've got a motor

00:14:09.833 --> 00:14:13.000
running, but some of that energy
goes into heat instead

00:14:13.000 --> 00:14:17.567
of turning the shaft of the
motor, that would be lost. But

00:14:17.567 --> 00:14:20.900
I think it would also include
your category, which is lost

00:14:20.900 --> 00:14:24.167
in the generation of
the electricity.

00:14:24.167 --> 00:14:25.567
Yeah, good point.

